{
  "texts": [
    "If a query is already precise, decomposition can introduce noise, and reranking cannot remove every irrelevant passage.",
    "Both modules also add computation, which may be prohibitive in low-latency scenarios.",
    "Performance further depends on the quality of the LLM used for sub-query generation and on an appropriate choice of reranker.",
    "Future work.",
    "Employing QD only when a query is predicted to need multi-hop reasoning could preserve most benefits while cutting overhead."
  ]
}